# Angular 18 Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Use standalone components (no NgModules for new code)
- Use signals for reactive state management
- Follow Angular CLI conventions: `ng generate component/service/pipe`
- Organize by feature modules, not by type

## Signals (Angular 16+)
- Use `signal()` for component state
- Use `computed()` for derived state
- Use `effect()` for side effects (sparingly)
- Use `input()` and `output()` signal-based APIs (Angular 17+)
- Migrate from `@Input()` decorators to `input()` function

## Modern Control Flow (Angular 17+)
- Use `@if` instead of `*ngIf`
- Use `@for` with `track` instead of `*ngFor` with `trackBy`
- Use `@switch` instead of `[ngSwitch]`
- Use `@defer` for lazy loading sections

## Services & Dependency Injection
- Use `providedIn: 'root'` for singleton services
- Use `inject()` function instead of constructor injection
- Create focused services: one responsibility per service

## Performance
- Use `OnPush` change detection strategy by default
- Use `@defer` blocks for below-the-fold content
- Use `trackBy` / `track` expression in loops
- Lazy load routes with `loadComponent` / `loadChildren`

## Forms
- Use Reactive Forms for complex forms, Template-driven for simple
- Always validate on both client and server
- Use strongly-typed forms with `FormGroup<T>`

## HTTP
- Use `HttpClient` with typed responses
- Implement interceptors for auth tokens, error handling, loading states
- Use `rxjs` operators: `switchMap`, `catchError`, `retry`
